-- Uruguay to Auction Seven Pluna Passenger Aircraft on Sept. 12
-- B y   L u c i a   B a l d o m i r
-- 2012-08-08T23:43:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-09/uruguay-to-auction-pluna-jets-as-flagship-carrier-still-grounded.html
Uruguay’s government plans to auction
seven Bombardier Inc. jets belonging to the  nation’s  Pluna
Lineas Aereas Uruguayas SA on Sept. 12.  The auction of the Bombardier CRJ900 Next Gen aircraft will
take place at Montevideo’s international airport and will begin
at $136.9 million, the government said in a statement on its
website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Baldomir in Montevideo at 
 lbaldomir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Philip Sanders at 
 psanders@bloomberg.net . 